overview: Biopic about famous gunslinger Wild Bill Hickock. The early career of legendary lawman is telescoped and culminates in his relocation in Deadwood and a reunion with Calamity Jane.
tagline: The Name Is Legendary. The Man Is Real.
title: Wild Bill

overview: Grant MacLaine, a former railroad troubleshooter, lost his job after letting his outlaw brother, the Utica Kid, escape. After spending five years wandering the west and earning his living playing the accordion, he is given a second chance by his former boss.
tagline: THE SAGA OF THE McLAINE BROTHERS!
title: Night Passage

overview: Things are different for the Pontipee men now that big brother Adam's fetched a bride and brought her to their cabin. Indeed, the unwed brothers are so inspired they raid the town and carry off brides of their own!
tagline: LUSTY, MIRTHFUL GIRL-STEALING MUSICAL! . . . with Seven Great Songs!
title: Seven Brides for Seven Brothers

overview: Based on the 1836 standoff between a group of Texan and Tejano men, led by Davy Crockett and Jim Bowie, and Mexican dictator Santa Anna's forces at the Alamo in San Antonio, Texas.
title: The Alamo

overview: Steven Spielberg executive produced this TNT miniseries about American Westward expansion during the 19th century. Told from both the perspective of the white Wheeler family and the Native American Lakota tribe, the 12-hour epic follows the clans as they struggle to find their place in a country confounded by turmoil and change.
title: Into the West

overview: Dare Rudd takes a shine to his cattleman cousin Tom's girlfriend who asks Tom to hire Dare to head the big cattle drive. Dare loses the money for the drive to cardsharps, but Tom wins it back, but Dare must save Tom's life.
title: Born to the West

overview: A wanted murderer, Billy John, is captured by Ben Brigade, a bounty hunter, who intends to take him to Santa Cruz to be hanged. Brigade stops at a staging post, where he saves the manager's wife from an Indian attack, and enlists the help of two outlaws to continue his journey more safely.
tagline: Scorching lead-hot action all the way!
title: Ride Lonesome

overview: A Dutch miner (Glenn Ford) and an Old West couple (Ida Lupino, Gig Young) die fighting over an Arizona gold mine lost in an earthquake.
tagline: Ruthless Fortune Seekers Who Will Stop at Nothing...
title: Lust for Gold

overview: John Martin is a government agent working under cover. Leading citizen Morgan calls in gunman Galt who blows Martin's cover.
title: Rainbow Valley

overview: Union spy Gail Loveless impersonates a black maid in the early days of the Civil War, but complications arise when she falls in love with a Confederate officer.
title: Operator 13

overview: A cowboy infiltrates a bandit hideout in search of his girlfriend's killer.
title: Rancho Notorious

overview: Scout William F. Cody (Joel McCrea) marries a U.S. senator's daughter (Maureen O'Hara), fights the Cheyenne and leads a Wild West show.
tagline: His adventure made him a hero.His showmanship made him a legend.
title: Buffalo Bill

overview: A stagecoach full of passengers and an enigmatic gunslinger are held hostage by two outlaws on the run from the law but events take an unexpected turn when the travelers are stalked by a mythical beast that only appears on the night of a blood red moon.
title: Blood Moon
